11 An Act relating to aeronautics; identifying original
appropriation; transferring remaining funds to the
12 Long-Term Aerospace and Aeronautics Infrastructure
Sustainability Revolving Fund; providing for
13 noncodification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20 Of the Fifty-seven Million Dollars ($57,000,000.00) appropriated
21 to the Oklahoma Department of Aerospace and Aeronautics in Section
22 72 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1125 of the 2nd Session of the 59th
23 Oklahoma Legislature, Forty-one Million Dollars ($41,000,000.00) or
24 so much as may be necessary shall be transferred to the Long-Term
Req. No. 17394 Page 1

1 Aero space and Aeronautics Infrastructure Sustainability Revolving
2 Fund created in Section 415 of Title 3 of the Oklahoma Statute.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
6 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
7 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
